# =============================================================================
# global.wqmignore.example — VERSION-CONTROLLED REFERENCE COPY
# =============================================================================
# The LIVE file the daemon reads is `dirname(WQM_DATABASE_PATH)/global.wqmignore`
# — bind-mounted from the gitignored `state/memexd/global.wqmignore` (see
# docker-compose.yml). Because `state/` is gitignored, the live copy is NOT under
# version control and is lost on a volume rebuild / machine move. Keep this
# example in sync as a backup. To restore: copy it to state/memexd/global.wqmignore
# and restart memexd (or touch any project .gitignore to trigger reconciliation).
# =============================================================================
# global.wqmignore — daemon-wide index exclusions
# =============================================================================
# Patterns here are applied to EVERY indexed project on top of each project's
# own .gitignore / .wqmignore. Uses standard gitignore syntax:
#
#   node_modules/   — exclude directory (trailing slash = dirs only)
#   *.zip           — exclude by extension
#   !important.log  — re-include a previously excluded path
#
# Changes take effect at the next ignore-file reconciliation event (triggered
# automatically when any project's .gitignore or .wqmignore is modified, or
# at the next daemon restart).
# =============================================================================

# testlink upstream sources (222 files). Use /** suffix — trailing-slash
# form `testlink/` was leaving files indexed (likely `add_ignore()` quirk).
# Re-include cfg/ and custom/ with /** matching contents explicitly.
**/bws-dev-plataform/testlink/**
# Re-include cfg/ and custom/. The DIRECTORY itself must be negated (trailing
# slash, no /**) in addition to its contents (/**): a directory-pruning walk
# tests the dir entry and, without the bare-dir negation, prunes cfg/ before
# descending — so the contents-only re-include never fires and the 14 cfg/custom
# files stay unindexed. Both forms together let the walk descend AND keep files.
!**/bws-dev-plataform/testlink/cfg/
!**/bws-dev-plataform/testlink/cfg/**
!**/bws-dev-plataform/testlink/custom/
!**/bws-dev-plataform/testlink/custom/**

**/zabbix/zabbix/**

# ─── Self-storage (Qdrant + memexd + MCP local state) ────────────────────────
# When the workspace-qdrant-mcp repo itself is indexed, the daemon would
# otherwise watch its own Qdrant storage / SQLite WAL / MCP logs, creating a
# feedback loop: Qdrant rotates a segment -> fs event -> enqueue Add/Delete ->
# daemon hits Qdrant -> Qdrant rotates more -> fs event -> ...
# Excluding the host-bind state dir breaks the loop.
state/
**/state/qdrant/
**/state/memexd/
**/state/mcp/
**/.fastembed_cache/

# ─── Build artifacts ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
build/
dist/
out/
target/
_build/
coverage/
**/coverage/
*.class
*.o
*.a
*.so
*.dylib
*.dll
*.exe
*.pdb

# ─── Dependency / vendor directories ─────────────────────────────────────────
node_modules/
vendors/
vendor/
bower_components/
jspm_packages/

# ─── Python virtual environments ─────────────────────────────────────────────
venv/
.venv/
env/
.env/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.Python

# ─── IDE / editor state ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Belt-and-suspenders: both anchored and **/ forms because the Rust `ignore`
# crate's add_ignore() treats patterns as anchored to the ignore-file's
# parent dir, not the walk root. Without **/ prefix, .claude/ would only
# match /home/memexd/.workspace-qdrant/.claude/ — NOT project-level .claude/.
.claude/
**/.claude/
.codex/
**/.codex/
.codex-skill-staging/
**/.codex-skill-staging/
.agents/
**/.agents/
.idea/
**/.idea/
.vscode/
**/.vscode/
*.iml
*.suo
*.ntvs_analysis.dat

# ─── Git internals (not auto-skipped when hidden=false) ──────────────────────
.git/
**/.git/

# ─── Toolchain caches ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.gradle/
**/.gradle/
.gradle-user/
**/.gradle-user/
.gradle-user-codex/
**/.gradle-user-codex/
.gradle-user-root/
**/.gradle-user-root/
.tools/
**/.tools/
.m2/
**/.m2/
.ivy2/
**/.ivy2/
.cargo/
**/.cargo/
.rustup/
**/.rustup/
.stack-work/
**/.stack-work/
# Flutter/Dart SDK checked into a project's tools/ dir (DOC-V2/tools/flutter =
# 3GB of framework .dart source). The `.tools/` patterns above only match the
# dotted form; an SDK under plain `tools/flutter/` leaks thousands of framework
# files into the embedding queue. Exclude the SDK subtree specifically (keeps
# real code under other tools/ dirs, e.g. src/rust/tools/registry-updater).
**/tools/flutter/**
**/flutter/bin/cache/**

# ─── Image / media assets (FastEmbed is text-only) ───────────────────────────
*.gif
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.ico
*.webp
*.svg
*.bmp
*.tiff
*.mp3
*.mp4
*.avi
*.mov
*.webm
*.wav
*.flac
*.ogg

# ─── Generated / large templates ─────────────────────────────────────────────
*.tpl

# ─── Archives and binary blobs ───────────────────────────────────────────────
*.zip
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.tar.bz2
*.tar.xz
*.tgz
*.gz
*.bz2
*.xz
*.7z
*.rar
*.jar
*.war
*.ear
*.iso
*.img
*.dmg

# ─── Generated / compiled assets ─────────────────────────────────────────────
*.min.js
*.min.css
*.bundle.js
*.map

# ─── Lock files (large, machine-generated) ───────────────────────────────────
# Confirmed culprits via `SELECT * FROM file_metadata ORDER BY size_bytes DESC`:
# pnpm-lock.yaml (464KB), package-lock.json (600KB).
package-lock.json
pnpm-lock.yaml
yarn.lock
# Cargo.lock                # opt-in: useful for grep in Rust workspaces
# Gemfile.lock
# poetry.lock

# ─── Generated proto / gRPC stubs ────────────────────────────────────────────
# protobuf-java emits *.java under generated dirs; same files re-emerge on
# every build. Search via `grep` on these is noise — the .proto source is
# what people actually want to look at.
**/proto/src/generated/
**/*_proto/
**/generated/proto/
# protobuf-java naming convention: outer class for a .proto file gets the
# suffix OuterClass.java (e.g. Profile.proto → ProfileOuterClass.java).
# Catches anything emitted under proto/doc/, proto/api/, proto/<anywhere>/.
**/*OuterClass.java
# protobuf-java message classes that DON'T get the OuterClass suffix still land
# under proto/<pkg>/ as generated holders (Shifts.java, User.java, Auth.java =
# 500KB/200KB each). 86 generated .java files under proto/ trees. The .proto
# source stays indexed; only the emitted Java is dropped.
**/proto/**/*.java

# ─── Generated protobuf — Dart (protoc-gen-dart) ─────────────────────────────
# 417 generated Dart bindings (shifts.pb.dart = 215KB etc.) with ZERO prior
# coverage. The .proto source is what people grep; these are pure codegen noise.
**/*.pb.dart
**/*.pbenum.dart
**/*.pbjson.dart
**/*.pbgrpc.dart
**/*.pbserver.dart

# ─── Generated code directories (broad) ──────────────────────────────────────
# 459 files under */generated/ across doc-backend (proto Java) and doc-frontend
# (packages/generated, lib/src/generated — proto Dart). Supersedes the narrow
# **/generated/proto/ above. If a project keeps hand-authored files under a
# generated/ dir, re-include them explicitly (e.g. !**/generated/keep.rs).
**/generated/
**/lib/src/generated/
**/packages/generated/

# ─── User uploads / dump dirs ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Conventional location for uploaded artifacts (CSV dumps, file uploads,
# database exports). Skip the whole subtree — legitimate code doesn't live
# under uploads/. If you DO have code in an uploads/ dir, add a re-include
# (e.g. `!**/uploads/keep.ts`).
**/uploads/

# ─── Test result dumps ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Playwright / Jest / Cypress emit massive JSON result files that can grow
# to hundreds of MB after a few runs.
**/e2e-results*.json
**/test-results*.json
**/playwright-report/
**/validation-reports/
**/test-artifacts/
**/backend-test-artifacts/

# ─── Generated third-party license bundles ───────────────────────────────────
# Rust `ignore` crate add_ignore() anchors to the ignore-file's parent dir,
# so we need the **/ prefix to match nested paths. See header comment above.
**/THIRD-PARTY-LICENSES.md
**/THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md
**/THIRD-PARTY-LICENSES.txt
**/LICENSE-3rdparty.json

# --- Semantic-search eval-artifact leakage (added 2026-06-02) ---
# The benchmark report + dataset contain the queries and expected paths
# verbatim; indexed, they dominate results. Project .wqmignore is not being
# honored on this ext4 setup, so exclude here (global IS applied).
**/mcp-server/reports/
**/benchmark-data/
**/mcp-server/scripts/benchmark-data/
**/semantic-search-quality.yaml

# --- workspace-qdrant-mcp: own test fixtures & generated assets (added 2026-06-09) ---
# Polyglot language-registry fixtures: a "bookshelf" sample app reimplemented in
# 20+ languages (142 files) plus a processing-pipeline corpus (31 files:
# HTML/txt/json/sample sources). These are CI fixtures for the dynamic language
# registry / extractor, NOT the daemon/MCP/CLI logic. Indexed, their generic
# symbols (models/storage/utils, "Book", "Shelf") and duplicated logic across
# every language flood semantic search for this repo. Project .wqmignore is not
# honored on this ext4 setup, so exclude globally — both paths are repo-specific
# enough to be safe across other indexed projects.
**/tests/language-support/
**/tests/artifacts/

# Grafana dashboard definitions — dense, machine-generated JSON (panel/query
# blobs), 9 files under docker/grafana/dashboards/ plus the assets/docs copies.
# Pure noise for code search.
**/grafana/dashboards/

# Vendored, patched copy of the upstream `fastembed` crate (src/rust/patches/
# fastembed, 44 files incl. its own .github/, README, tests). Third-party code
# that competes with the daemon's real embedding modules in search results.
# Uncomment to drop it from the index; leave it if you actively grep the patch.
# **/src/rust/patches/fastembed/
